cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): This paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) and specifically on medication extraction from clinical text notes. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The system evaluated in this paper, Amazon Comprehend Medical, is a deep learning based system. The paper also discusses the use of benchmark datasets and tools to establish and confirm expected quality of results, which is a common topic in machine learning. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper discusses the extraction of clinical concepts from text notes, which can be seen as a form of information retrieval. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The use of deep learning in Amazon Comprehend Medical falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper briefly mentions the importance of trust and validation in new data products, which can be seen as a societal issue related to the use of technology in healthcare.
